d holds an MBA from University of California Los Angeles and a degree in Business Administration from University of California Berkeley. A recipient of the Wittenberg-Livingston Fellowship, Richard is also a member of the esteemed Beta Gamma Sigma Business Honorary Society.Specialties: With over 35 years of experience in the investment banking sector, Richard’s specialties lie in the areas of:•	Investment Banking•	Structured IPO•	Middle Market Companies•	Emerging Growth CompaniesExperienceCEOWestPark Capital, Inc.1999  –  Present (18 years)Richard is CEO and Founder of WestPark Capital – an investment bank specializing in emerging growth sectors and focusing in the fields of healthcare, software, technology, biotechnology, financial services, manufacturing, consumer products, media, telecom industries, and more. Using the revolutionary “SIPO” process, which Richard and the firm created, WestPark Capital has taken hundreds of companies public. As CEO, Richard manages the daily operations of WestPark, including administration, direction and coordination of the firm. In this role, Richard provides strategic leadership; development of WestPark’s vision and mission; implementation of policies; strategic thinking; oversight of the financial management and effective use of financial resources; people management; maintaining effective relationships with clients, partners and employees; supervising senior staff members; adhering to policies and procedures; and, complying with government regulations.Managing Director, Investment BankingGlobal Capital Securities1997  –  1999 (2 years)Prior to establishing WestPark Capital, Richard was Manager Director of Investment Banking at Global Capital Securities – an investment banking and securities brokerage firm. In this role, Richard headed the North American Investment Banking departments and was responsible for all aspects of the firm’s corporate finance activities.  As Managing Director, Richard managed existing clients and current deals, including closing deals. He was also responsible for developing new business for the firm, marketing services to clients, and establishing sales and marketing strategies.Managing Director, Investment BankingJoseph Charles & Associates1994  –  1997 (3 years)Richard was Managing Director of Investment Banking at Joseph Charles & Associates for four years. During this time, Richard managed the firm’s finances and led the investment banking department. Managing DirectorHJ Meyers & Co (Beverly Hills)1987  –  1995 (8 years)Richard’s role involved new business development and managing of the firm’s public offerings.  While in this position, Richard completed more than 25 public offerings and numerous private transactions.CertificationsGeneral Securities Representative (GS) LicenseFinancial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA), License Securities License - Series 7Limited Representative - Investment BankerFinancial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA), License Securities Licence - Series 79General Securities PrincipalFinancial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA), License Securities Licence - Series 24Uniform Securities Agent LicenseFinancial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA), License Securities Licence - Series 63Limited Representative  – Equity TraderFinancial Industry Regulatory Authority (FINRA), License Securities License - Series 55EducationUniversity of California, Los AngelesMaster of Business Administration (M.B.A.)Master of Business Administration (M.B.A.)1986  –  1988Richard completed a Master of Business Administration at the University of California Los Angeles (UCLA). With over 5,000 courses on offer, the University received a 2014 ranking of 10th in the Times Higher Education World Reputation Rankings and a 2014/2015 ranking of 12th in The World University Rankings by The Times of London.  Additional rankings for UCLA have included 12th in the Academic Ranking of World Universities (Shanghai Jiao Tong University), 23rd in the 2015 U.S. News & 