Richard Rappaport Chief Executive Officer and Founder


Check the background of investment professionals associated with this site on FINRA’s BrokerCheck






Phone Number (310) 843 9300












Richard Rappaport 
 Richard Rappaport founded WestPark Capital in Los Angeles, California, in 1999.
Prior to establishing WestPark Capital, Mr. Rappaport had over 25 years of extensive experience in the small capital investment banking and securities markets. Throughout his substantial career, Mr.Rappaport has completed the financing of hundreds of companies – both in the United States and internationally.
Read more 

Previous to launching WestPark Capital, Mr. Rappaport was the Managing Director of Investment Banking at internationally based Global Capital Securities, and was Managing Director of Investment Banking at Joseph Charles & Associates from 1995 to 1999.  During his time at both firms, Mr. Rappaport led the investment banking departments and was chiefly responsible for all aspects of corporate financial activities.
From 1987 to 1995, Mr. Rappaport held the Managing Directorship at a Beverly Hills-based boutique Investment Bank.  Here he was responsible for all aspects of the firm’s public offerings, including new business development.  Additionally during this period, Mr. Rappaport completed over 25 public offerings and numerous private transactions.
Mr. Rappaport holds a B.S. in Business Administration from the University of California at Berkeley, and an M.B.A. from the University of California at Los Angeles.  At UCLA, Mr. Rappaport received the Wittenberg-Livingston Fellowship and became a member of the revered Beta Gamma Sigma Business Honorary Society.


